WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:15.871 --> 00:02:17.668
Jump! Jump!

3
00:02:18.846 --> 00:02:19.405
Higher!

4
00:02:21.680 --> 00:02:23.105
So. well done!

5
00:02:24.192 --> 00:02:24.909
Smarty!

6
00:04:42.295 --> 00:04:43.994
Dad. can I go look?

7
00:04:44.516 --> 00:04:45.625
Oh. please!

8
00:04:45.662 --> 00:04:47.442
Okay. I'll go and park the car

9
00:04:47.870 --> 00:04:48.804
Just do not run!

10
00:04:48.840 --> 00:04:49.433
Okay!

11
00:07:45.996 --> 00:07:50.471
You never know when it will happen.
from the moment you enter the world you are trying to reach the end.

12
00:07:50.508 --> 00:07:55.464
whatever we do will come back to haunt us
It's like a curse. For life.

13
00:07:55.500 --> 00:07:58.350
bloodshed is never the answer

14
00:07:59.049 --> 00:08:00.673
Spilled blood never dries

15
00:08:01.021 --> 00:08:02.872
Do you hear? Never!

16
00:08:03.581 --> 00:08:08.389
Spill it and live life in fear.
Relax for a moment - and you're gone.

17
00:08:11.565 --> 00:08:13.124
Prison - this is the end game.

18
00:08:14.522 --> 00:08:16.607
We end up here because of stupidity or bad luck.

19
00:08:17.124 --> 00:08:19.508
... a month later you're out.
all is forgotten ...

20
00:08:19.509 --> 00:08:21.190
And you will return
a normal person.

21
00:08:25.881 --> 00:08:27.699
Eli. on you're way..out.

22
00:08:35.494 --> 00:08:38.345
And believe me.
it's better never to return

23
00:08:43.310 --> 00:08:45.022
You're a good kid. Charles.

24
00:09:34.076 --> 00:09:37.193
Goldman. Eli. killed in the line
of duty.

25
00:09:44.677 --> 00:09:46.484
Multiple gunshot wound's. Breathing fucked.

26
00:09:46.520 --> 00:09:48.376
Cardiovascular...bollocksed

27
00:09:50.841 --> 00:09:52.951
Heart rhythm slowing.
We're losing him!

28
00:10:04.766 --> 00:10:05.650
When did you find him?

29
00:10:05.651 --> 00:10:06.634
Ten minutes ago.

30
00:10:07.205 --> 00:10:07.913
Pulse. blood pressure?

31
00:10:08.105 --> 00:10:10.080
Pulse 70. pressure 90 over 60.

32
00:10:10.116 --> 00:10:10.814
What time?

33
00:10:10.851 --> 00:10:11.848
I need adrenaline.

34
00:10:25.439 --> 00:10:26.987
Crazy with your asses!

35
00:10:27.023 --> 00:10:31.169
And he said: "Just don't
talk about what you don't know"

36
00:10:31.604 --> 00:10:33.723
And then the mayor. thinking. says ...

37
00:10:37.569 --> 00:10:40.745
Do what you have to do with these
asses they are completely confused.

38
00:10:41.704 --> 00:10:45.405
I do not understand what is at stake.
what we're arguing about!

39
00:10:46.570 --> 00:10:47.336
Do you smoke?

40
00:10:53.133 --> 00:10:54.263
You're smoking in my house?

41
00:10:59.114 --> 00:10:59.572
Hello!

42
00:11:00.531 --> 00:11:01.131
Hello!

43
00:11:03.481 --> 00:11:04.005
Hello!

44
00:11:07.298 --> 00:11:07.791
What?

45
00:11:08.906 --> 00:11:09.890
It is bad.

46
00:11:10.640 --> 00:11:11.628
I'll call back.

47
00:11:15.690 --> 00:11:17.991
Yes. He died?

48
00:11:21.375 --> 00:11:22.591
Thanks for the call.

49
00:11:23.406 --> 00:11:26.090
Monsieur Martineri.
First you have to knock!

50
00:11:26.292 --> 00:11:29.635
This is a matter of extreme importance.
otherwise I would not bother you.

51
00:11:29.671 --> 00:11:32.067
regarding the negative tax returns

52
00:11:33.193 --> 00:11:34.515
You knock before you come in here!

53
00:11:36.843 --> 00:11:37.693
You understand French no?

54
00:11:39.005 --> 00:11:41.904
If you can't use your hands I'll take them from you.
so you still deaf!

55
00:11:41.941 --> 00:11:44.506
Fuck off out. knock. ask and enter

56
00:11:54.036 --> 00:11:55.172
Can I come in?

57
00:12:08.676 --> 00:12:10.487
Tweezers! Clip!

58
00:12:13.544 --> 00:12:18.837
Charlie Matei. 57 year old and considered one
of the crime lords of the city ...

59
00:12:18.838 --> 00:12:21.246
is in intensive care at Timon hospital
following a shooting earlier today.

60
00:12:21.282 --> 00:12:23.359
Under heavy police guard.

61
00:12:23.523 --> 00:12:24.472
Give me Goldman.

62
00:12:25.985 --> 00:12:27.643
Matei suffered multiple injuries. but has survived the attack.

63
00:12:28.251 --> 00:12:34.201
For three years Matei struggled to win a crime war
seizing power from other bosses.

64
00:12:34.238 --> 00:12:37.064
He heads an organisation also with Bosses
Tony and Aurelio Rampaul.

65
00:12:37.101 --> 00:12:41.088
Matei has always escaped justice for his alleged criminal activities

66
00:12:41.125 --> 00:12:45.279
Rumour has it that Charles Matei recently retired from his life of crime...

67
00:12:45.316 --> 00:12:48.572
And devoted his life to his family.
wife Christel and two children.

68
00:12:48.609 --> 00:12:51.363
No. no. sir.
Working professionals.

69
00:12:51.614 --> 00:12:54.000
In the old port we've now found
Two stolen cars.

70
00:12:55.697 --> 00:12:57.581
Do you know who did this. do you have any clues to this attack?

71
00:13:02.176 --> 00:13:04.226
...received an anonymous call
and it's crawling with journalists..

72
00:13:04.263 --> 00:13:08.339
No. sir..an anonymous call.

73
00:13:09.657 --> 00:13:10.549
No. sir ...

74
00:13:12.357 --> 00:13:14.919
You think that I like
working in such conditions?

75
00:13:19.037 --> 00:13:22.195
Yes. sorry. Of course. sir.
I will do everything I can.

76
00:13:22.679 --> 00:13:23.386
I'll call.

77
00:13:31.227 --> 00:13:33.035
"Now then. you remember what I told you. you remember?

78
00:13:35.078 --> 00:13:36.335
I'm in a hurry. I don't have much time

79
00:13:36.372 --> 00:13:39.302
Yes. I remember Aurelio.
you told me that I should never ...

80
00:13:39.339 --> 00:13:41.871
No. no. Bertrand. what exactly did I tell you?

81
00:13:41.908 --> 00:13:43.988
Repeat. word for word. it's important to be exact.
Words have meaning.

82
00:13:44.025 --> 00:13:47.256
You said...Bertrand.
I want to trust you.

83
00:13:47.293 --> 00:13:48.347
We're friends.

84
00:13:48.384 --> 00:13:49.215
We're friends?

85
00:13:49.632 --> 00:13:50.439
We're friends.

86
00:13:50.884 --> 00:13:51.760
Yes. friends..

87
00:13:51.796 --> 00:13:52.759
exactly!

88
00:13:53.217 --> 00:13:55.233
I want to trust you.
we're friends!

89
00:13:55.882 --> 00:13:59.250
But I'm scared. you said I am the black sheep of the family!

90
00:13:59.287 --> 00:14:00.600
You are! Well. Bertrand..tell me

91
00:14:01.034 --> 00:14:04.112
What did I tell you...exactly

92
00:14:04.597 --> 00:14:05.192
said..

93
00:14:05.194 --> 00:14:05.730
Yeah.

94
00:14:06.514 --> 00:14:08.181
You said that if I take one single gram..

95
00:14:08.218 --> 00:14:09.673
or even a little less than a gram

96
00:14:10.964 --> 00:14:12.474
It would be a matter of principle!

97
00:14:12.511 --> 00:14:15.144
You see. I remember the same.
Wait. excuse me.

98
00:14:15.181 --> 00:14:19.279
I beg you Aurelio. I did fuck all!
I did not take any! I must have a hole in the pocket!
Do not kill me..

99
00:14:23.387 --> 00:14:24.819
Yes. now I can hear better.

100
00:14:25.370 --> 00:14:25.854
Yes.

101
00:14:34.245 --> 00:14:36.780
Hey. guys. they say. Matei was
shot in the old port.

102
00:14:36.963 --> 00:14:37.756
They shot him.

103
00:14:37.793 --> 00:14:38.698
Is he dead?

104
00:14:38.734 --> 00:14:40.298
Not sure

105
00:14:48.016 --> 00:14:48.817
Scissors!

106
00:14:50.700 --> 00:14:51.318
Tweezers!

107
00:15:00.424 --> 00:15:02.036
We Interrupt this program to bring you a breaking news story

108
00:15:02.282 --> 00:15:06.834
Mark Aldmano. one of the most prominent underworld leaders.
nicknamed Ein..

109
00:15:06.835 --> 00:15:09.244
was gunned down and  killed at a bar in Lenzh square.

110
00:15:09.664 --> 00:15:14.741
A police source said that this appeared to be a contract mafia killing.

111
00:15:24.876 --> 00:15:26.150
Good afternoon. Mr. Fernandez.

112
00:15:28.272 --> 00:15:30.188
Monsieur Fernandez. M. Fernandez!

113
00:15:30.225 --> 00:15:32.157
Au revoir. monsieur Fernandez.

114
00:15:48.577 --> 00:15:49.412
Are you fucking mad?

115
00:15:49.878 --> 00:15:52.353
Killing Fernandez - is like
killing the Pope.

116
00:15:52.389 --> 00:15:54.895
So. then we kill the Pope!

117
00:16:00.644 --> 00:16:01.819
We vow to be friends to death!

118
00:16:04.561 --> 00:16:05.944
We vow to be friends until death.

119
00:16:14.537 --> 00:16:15.774
We vow to be friends until death.

120
00:16:45.874 --> 00:16:47.876
Papa! Papa!

121
00:17:08.409 --> 00:17:09.743
What do you know about Matei's personal life?

122
00:17:09.779 --> 00:17:12.909
10 years ago. when I first joined the police.

123
00:17:13.251 --> 00:17:15.068
He just got with his second wife.

124
00:17:15.493 --> 00:17:16.201
And the first?

125
00:17:17.329 --> 00:17:20.637
they were together a long time.
had a daughter. and then ...

126
00:17:21.163 --> 00:17:23.122
she was ill & ended up with his lawyer Martin Bodinar.

127
00:17:23.781 --> 00:17:25.298
The second wife?

128
00:17:25.335 --> 00:17:27.690
An old prostitute...
Christelle Kolarovo.

129
00:17:28.089 --> 00:17:29.590
She worked for a pimp. called Pistachio

130
00:17:30.077 --> 00:17:32.734
Matei fell in love with her.
decided to make a life with her...

131
00:17:33.294 --> 00:17:36.168
Bought her from the pimp. cleaned her up. she bore him a child.

132
00:17:57.787 --> 00:17:58.704
Marie Goldman.

133
00:18:04.071 --> 00:18:06.338
Some people think we have nothing better to do in the city

134
00:18:06.374 --> 00:18:08.113
That we only have social work to do...

135
00:18:08.589 --> 00:18:11.552
stay low key. shake down immigrants and keep them on their toes.

136
00:18:12.452 --> 00:18:14.661
You know... Louis XIV. He took Marseille..

137
00:18:14.697 --> 00:18:19.653
He surrounded the city walls. they gave him hell with heavy guns
from the forts Saint-Jean and San Nicolas.

138
00:18:20.794 --> 00:18:22.269
What did it teach us? do you know?

139
00:18:22.575 --> 00:18:25.326
You know the motto of Louis XIV?

140
00:18:26.076 --> 00:18:27.585
Well. no. sir.

141
00:18:28.003 --> 00:18:31.278
Louis XIV used to say:
The winner is the man who remains patient.

142
00:18:32.421 --> 00:18:33.374
And I agree with him.

143
00:18:33.497 --> 00:18:37.022
To clean all the shite out in this town
we need to be patient.

144
00:18:37.059 --> 00:18:39.648
They want to kill each other?
Let them kill themselves.

145
00:18:39.685 --> 00:18:41.631
makes our job and our lives easier. I think so..

146
00:18:42.181 --> 00:18:43.848
I thought
we are engaged in an investigation.

147
00:18:43.884 --> 00:18:48.590
Minimally Goldman. our task - is to protect
decent people.

148
00:18:48.626 --> 00:18:51.570
And if gangsters want to kill each other and end up dead...

149
00:18:52.162 --> 00:18:52.997
Matei dead?

150
00:18:53.398 --> 00:18:54.530
No. he came out of the coma.

151
00:18:54.567 --> 00:18:57.711
Interrogate him. if he remembers.
he was attacked - all well and good.

152
00:18:57.747 --> 00:18:59.295
If not - then so be it.

153
00:18:59.332 --> 00:19:02.186
anyway. Stick to the rules..this is not about you.

154
00:19:02.223 --> 00:19:02.830
Goldman!

155
00:19:03.854 --> 00:19:05.303
Do not turn this into a personal war.

156
00:19:07.079 --> 00:19:11.630
Your husband was a really exceptional police officer
but sometimes it is too risky to live in the past.

157
00:19:12.196 --> 00:19:14.537
What's done is done. revenge...it's a nonsense

158
00:19:15.080 --> 00:19:17.364
His killer remained unpunished.
that's the nonsense!

159
00:19:26.033 --> 00:19:27.407
Do you remember anything of the attackers?

160
00:19:29.516 --> 00:19:30.810
Maybe you knew someone?

161
00:19:32.582 --> 00:19:36.015
Monsieur Matei. if you want
us to find them. help us.

162
00:19:36.438 --> 00:19:38.847
You know they will come for you again.

163
00:19:38.883 --> 00:19:41.869
Sure we can leave a guard outside.
but that won't stop them.

164
00:19:42.428 --> 00:19:43.445
Let's agree. let's work together

165
00:19:50.463 --> 00:19:51.041
No.

166
00:19:55.788 --> 00:19:57.979
No. no. no! Good day. sir.

167
00:19:58.247 --> 00:20:00.513
Don't come here without informing me
about your visits in advance.

168
00:20:00.549 --> 00:20:01.412
It's my job.

169
00:20:01.724 --> 00:20:02.531
I don't want to bother you.

170
00:20:03.407 --> 00:20:06.057
Give your client some advice. helping
us - is in his best interests.

171
00:20:07.363 --> 00:20:07.948
Good day.

172
00:20:10.689 --> 00:20:11.687
Look who I brought.

173
00:20:19.323 --> 00:20:19.856
Mom ...

174
00:20:22.310 --> 00:20:24.379
when you die.
is it forever?

175
00:20:25.021 --> 00:20:26.305
Yes. son. this is forever

176
00:20:27.281 --> 00:20:29.274
So
Dad will always remain in the ground?

177
00:20:33.279 --> 00:20:34.079
No..

178
00:20:45.247 --> 00:20:45.973
Your daddy ...

179
00:20:46.981 --> 00:20:48.720
Your father in heaven

180
00:20:49.813 --> 00:20:52.029
He is proud of you and watches as you are growing.

181
00:20:53.905 --> 00:20:54.997
He is happy for you.

182
00:20:55.034 --> 00:20:55.724
He sees me?

183
00:20:55.761 --> 00:20:56.816
Yes. he see's.

184
00:20:56.853 --> 00:20:58.056
And under the sofa too?

185
00:20:58.483 --> 00:21:00.509
Yes. and under the sofa. too.

186
00:21:00.546 --> 00:21:02.458
why doesn't he call us?

187
00:21:04.297 --> 00:21:08.882
Because there is no phone
but still he sees you and is happy.

188
00:21:10.472 --> 00:21:11.997
He sees and hears you.

189
00:21:13.381 --> 00:21:14.716
Go to sleep. my darling.

190
00:21:16.699 --> 00:21:17.448
I love you.

191
00:21:27.048 --> 00:21:27.549
Hello.

192
00:21:30.147 --> 00:21:30.706
Hello!

193
00:21:53.760 --> 00:21:55.784
Charlie is alive but we can't move him anywhere.

194
00:21:56.117 --> 00:21:58.878
We can't just do nothing and wait for them to finish him off..

195
00:21:59.411 --> 00:22:00.410
I don't know what to do for the best.

196
00:22:01.093 --> 00:22:02.436
So.  for now we cannot do anything.

197
00:22:02.472 --> 00:22:03.836
We can't leave it like this. that's impossible!

198
00:22:04.851 --> 00:22:05.635
What can we do?

199
00:22:06.183 --> 00:22:07.879
Burn Marsailles down?
Raise an army?

200
00:22:08.054 --> 00:22:09.488
There are only three of us...

201
00:22:16.697 --> 00:22:18.333
we cannot just leave him to be picked off.

202
00:22:22.317 --> 00:22:24.002
Learn. my friend. listen to teammates.

203
00:23:19.080 --> 00:23:21.586
What have they done?
What they do to him?

204
00:23:43.476 --> 00:23:44.195
He's getting better.

205
00:23:44.231 --> 00:23:45.837
But he can't sing for shit.

206
00:24:08.252 --> 00:24:08.769
All right.

207
00:24:51.244 --> 00:24:54.493
This place is full of infection..
better to be safe than sorry.

208
00:25:05.804 --> 00:25:07.679
I'm going have a smoke.
I will not bother you.

209
00:25:12.137 --> 00:25:13.238
How can we care for you?

210
00:25:14.804 --> 00:25:17.189
Remember that I'm always close.

211
00:25:17.348 --> 00:25:18.775
Christelle needn't be worried.

212
00:25:23.569 --> 00:25:27.010
I brought flowers. to make this place more bearable.
but doctors forbade me from bringing them.

213
00:25:28.293 --> 00:25:28.973
Yo!

214
00:25:29.176 --> 00:25:29.898
Open the door!

215
00:25:31.065 --> 00:25:32.615
Show him the flowers!

216
00:25:34.846 --> 00:25:35.465
Look!

217
00:25:38.159 --> 00:25:39.608
It's a pity so beautiful.

218
00:25:39.818 --> 00:25:40.400
Yes.

219
00:25:40.808 --> 00:25:41.827
enough. shut the door!

220
00:25:43.360 --> 00:25:45.266
Don't worry. the most important thing is that you are alive.

221
00:25:46.191 --> 00:25:46.900
This is important.

222
00:25:46.936 --> 00:25:49.068
And all things considered you look quite good
Seriously!

223
00:25:49.217 --> 00:25:51.325
Even after twenty-two bullets!

224
00:25:51.957 --> 00:25:53.999
And after 2 weeks you can already walk.

225
00:25:54.036 --> 00:25:57.700
Look at me. Shot to fucking bits. wrinkles. shakes
Yes. I had the shakes!

226
00:25:58.266 --> 00:26:00.236
I was so worried. frightened! Shows on my face here!

227
00:26:01.103 --> 00:26:02.054
Even with the glasses on.

228
00:26:04.837 --> 00:26:06.562
Look what I brought you from Notre Dame.

229
00:26:07.952 --> 00:26:11.345
This is the Holy martyr and defender of the flock.

230
00:26:11.381 --> 00:26:13.226
He is also a powerful healer.

231
00:26:17.452 --> 00:26:20.585
They say when you feel bad.
He hugs you.

232
00:26:20.585 --> 00:26:22.050
Microphones-cameras-fake ambulance-cops

233
00:26:28.130 --> 00:26:30.521
You're my brother. Charles. I'll find these
bastards. I promise!

234
00:26:37.083 --> 00:26:37.823
Thank you.

235
00:26:47.667 --> 00:26:48.753
This is for you..chocolate's.

236
00:26:56.167 --> 00:26:58.892
Understand me correctly.
I can not give him anesthetics.

237
00:26:58.893 --> 00:26:59.732
Why is that?

238
00:26:59.768 --> 00:27:01.580
His nerves in his hands are damaged. very sensitive.

239
00:27:01.616 --> 00:27:03.415
I need him to stay awake

240
00:27:04.067 --> 00:27:07.141
To speak while I work he must remain awake.
he should not feel pain.

241
00:27:07.317 --> 00:27:08.268
Oh..and by the way

242
00:27:09.108 --> 00:27:10.000
This X-ray

243
00:27:11.893 --> 00:27:13.068
He swallowed a gun?

244
00:27:13.613 --> 00:27:17.222
Are you fucking stupid? we put the x-ray machine
directly above his bed.

245
00:27:17.919 --> 00:27:19.195
It's under the mattress....Sherlock.

246
00:27:32.883 --> 00:27:37.490
Sleep. my beautiful baby.
Baiushki-hush.

247
00:27:37.526 --> 00:27:42.373
Quiet baby looks bright
in your cradle.

248
00:28:13.827 --> 00:28:15.742
He gave you fuck all
but you still love him.

249
00:28:17.743 --> 00:28:20.452
What can I do if you have
such a big heart.

250
00:28:20.800 --> 00:28:24.209
And it is growing. they called him crazy.
now..he's immortal.

251
00:28:24.852 --> 00:28:26.085
It's a big jump.

252
00:28:28.111 --> 00:28:29.637
I don't want to live without you!

253
00:28:35.175 --> 00:28:36.326
He sends kisses.

254
00:28:41.558 --> 00:28:42.984
But did you finally relax!

255
00:28:45.150 --> 00:28:46.991
Come on. everybody is at ease now.

